What is the structure of my dataset?¶

  • There are 183412 fordgobike trips in the dataset
  • There are 16 factors within trips : ( duration_sec, start_time, end_time, start_station_id, start_station_name, start_station_latitude, start_station_longitude, end_station_id, end_station_name, end_station_latitude ,end_station_longitude, bike_id, user_type, member_birth_year, member_gender and bike_share_for_all_trip )

What is/are the main feature(s) of interest in my dataset?¶

  • Finding out how trip duration is dependent on other factors .

What features in the dataset do I think will help support my investigation into my feature(s) of interest?¶

  • I think that trip duration is dependent on the start stations, end stations ( because more crowded places receive more riders ), user type, birth year and gender also may effect trip duration.

2- Univariate Exploration :¶

I'll look at the distribution of the main factor of interest: duration_sec and other factors: start_station_id, end_station_id, member_birth_year, member_gender and user_type.
